<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id52cd242b-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6" identifier="/us/usc/t28/s2102"><num value="2102">§ 2102.</num><heading> Priority of criminal case on appeal from State court</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Criminal cases on review from State courts shall have priority, on the docket of the Supreme Court, over all cases except cases to which the United States is a party and such other cases as the court may decide to be of public importance.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id52cd242c-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">(<ref href="/us/act/1948-06-25/ch646">June 25, 1948, ch. 646</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/62/962">62 Stat. 962</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id52cd242d-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="historicalAndRevision" id="id52cd242e-3a70-11f1-9e0c-dcbb1364dae6"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Historical and Revision Notes</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Based on title 28, U.S.C., 1940 ed., § 351 (<ref href="/us/act/1911-03-03/ch231/s253">Mar. 3, 1911, ch. 231, § 253</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/36/1160">36 Stat. 1160</ref>; <ref href="/us/act/1928-01-31/ch14/s1">Jan. 31, 1928, ch. 14, § 1</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/45/54">45 Stat. 54</ref>).</p>
